annotationA: Eukaryotic translation initiation factor 2 subunit 2; eIF-2 functions in the early steps of protein synthesis by forming a ternary complex with GTP and initiator tRNA. This preinitiation complex mediates ribosomal recognition of a start codon during the scanning process of the leader region
annotationB: eIF5B, isoform B; Protein binding; GTPase activity; translation initiation factor activity; DEAD/H-box RNA helicase binding; GTP binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: translational initiation
